  "body": "Erigon version: ```erigon version 2022.08.3-alpha-defbddf8```\r\n\r\nI am using erigon + nimbus, and y'day Erigon stopped to work:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSep 04 21:01:01 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:01:01.784] [NewPayload] Previously known bad block  hash=0x9b201dbc5b73d786c11042aa1a5d616b7c5ce2b8305fd3e13c565ac99c08a10f\r\nSep 04 21:01:11 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:01:11.473] [NewPayload] Previously known bad block  hash=0x9b201dbc5b73d786c11042aa1a5d616b7c5ce2b8305fd3e13c565ac99c08a10f\r\n```\r\n\r\n30 min later:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nSep 04 21:32:11 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:32:11.898] Skipping payload building because forkchoiceState.headBlockHash is not the head of the canonical chain forkChoice.HeadBlockHash=0x165d6abf3d496aaebead2c066d392d3248dda2c7303>\r\nSep 04 21:32:13 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:32:13.639] Skipping payload building because forkchoiceState.headBlockHash is not the head of the canonical chain forkChoice.HeadBlockHash=0x5124749aa0987187bd2125a4e186185323eeb143b9e>\r\nSep 04 21:32:15 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:32:15.492] Skipping payload building because forkchoiceState.headBlockHash is not the head of the canonical chain forkChoice.HeadBlockHash=0x2cc0e81a6b4cf97ed76b986ca6ad90d7a95e46f6345>\r\nSep 04 21:32:17 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:32:17.125] Skipping payload building because forkchoiceState.headBlockHash is not the head of the canonical chain forkChoice.HeadBlockHash=0xc2fb0fd751d5f31ffd67ce0452b8fe80cd91273b7b1>\r\nSep 04 21:32:18 erigon[7149]: [WARN] [09-04|21:32:18.972] Skipping payload building because forkchoiceState.headBlockHash is not the head of the canonical chain forkChoice.HeadBlockHash=0x499d782b6806413389887bba0f88a8bc39b83c386e0>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd it's been 12h since  it keeps looping printing the above errors \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn the consensus client side (Nimbus), it crashed and cannot be started anymore, reported on https://github.com/status-im/nimbus-eth2/issues/4063",
